This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category as it discusses bandwidth reservation and quality of service guarantees in MPLS-based networks. It may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category as it deals with traffic prioritization and sharing among different classes. Additionally, it could be classified under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it proposes a new bandwidth allocation model for improving network utilization. Information Theory (cs.IT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) are also possible sub-categories as they deal with the efficient use of network resources and traffic management.
